<item>
            <title>[LU-16460] fix lnetctl command line option bugs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16460</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While moving LNet to netlink in my testing of different lnetctl command options bugs were exposed. Some of the bugs are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) A double free in the kernel when settting up a LNet NI for an interface that doesn&apos; exis.t&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) NI tunables not being properly set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) A memory leak when registering a LNet NI twice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4) Better range handling of user input and less strict failing for bad parameters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Any LNet setup.</environment>
